      <div class="text-left text-sm text-darkGrey space-y-6">
        <p>
          MirageOS started with funding in 2009 from the <a class="link-blue" href="http://www.rcuk.ac.uk/">RCUK</a> <a class="link-blue" href="http://horizon.ac.uk">Horizon Digital Economy</a> Research Hub grant,
          <a class="link-blue" href="http://gow.epsrc.ac.uk/NGBOViewGrant.aspx?GrantRef=EP/G065802/1">EP/G065802/1</a>. Amazon also granted us an <a class="link-blue" href="http://aws.amazon.com/education/">Amazon in Education</a> award and Verisign
          <a class="link-blue" href="http://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/news/2011/03/anil-madhavapeddy-wins-verisign-grant/">sponsored</a> work via an <a class="link-blue" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5-4lbyD_Fvw">Internet Infrastructure Award</a>, and
          <a class="link-blue" href="http://www.rackspace.com/cloud/">Rackspace</a> gives us developer resources on their cloud. Work has also been supported by the <a class="link-blue" href="http://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/research/srg/netos/mrc2/">MRC2</a> and
          <a class="link-blue" href="http://ocaml.io">OCaml Labs</a> projects.
        </p>
        <p>
          The research leading to this code has also received funding from the European Union's Seventh Framework Programme FP7/2007-2013 under the <a class="link-blue" href="http://www.trilogy2.eu/">Trilogy 2</a> project (grant agreement no 317756) and the
          <a class="link-blue" href="http://usercentricnetworking.eu/">User Centric Networking</a> project (grant agreement no 611001). Publications are <a class="link-blue" href="/docs/papers">open access</a>.
        </p>
